I always kind of dread day 6, and I can't even count how many times I've done a 30 day journey. My neck and throat tend to get really sore, because my head is rather large (I feel a bit like a baby that can't hold up its own head) and heavy. Today, zero issue. My magic solution: don't work so hard. I am able to lift my shoulderblades of the ground now, but that's because I did it many many times without doing that. So I took a step back and just did the most intense movement that still felt comfortable. This is going to help me no longer dread day 6 and stick with it... Because it's better to modulate down than to quit.

Thanks Adriene. Yesterday was my day 6 but I really struggled. I spent a large part of the session just laying on my mat, unable to continue, but I stuck out to the end, doing what I could. So I decided to repeat day 6 today. What seemed impossible yesterday, I could do today, recognising that some days are more difficult than others and the secret to success is not giving up, but trying again. Some days are better than others,  on the yoga mat and off. We just need to give ourselves a second chance, or even a third, or fourth, if necessary. I discovered you during the lockdown period here in South Africa and you helped me to stay sane, in more ways than one. I hope you know how many people from all over the world you are helping with your yoga channel, not just with your yoga lessons, but also your words. You are providing much needed therapy. Best wishes.
